					<section class="content-section">
						<h2>What is GMAX Testing?</h2>
						<div class="section-content">
							<p>GMAX (Gravity Maximum) testing measures the maximum deceleration experienced when a standard mass impacts an artificial turf surface. Think of it as measuring how "hard" your field hits back when a player lands on it.</p>
							
							<div class="highlight-box">
								<h3>The Science Behind GMAX</h3>
								<p>The test uses a specialized missile that simulates a human head impact. The resulting measurement indicates the potential for head injuries - the higher the GMAX reading, the greater the risk.</p>
							</div>

							<h3>GMAX Standards</h3>
							<ul>
								<li><strong>Below 165g:</strong> Optimal safety range</li>
								<li><strong>165-200g:</strong> Acceptable but requires monitoring</li>
								<li><strong>Above 200g:</strong> Unsafe - immediate action required</li>
								<li><strong>Above 325g:</strong> Extremely dangerous - field should be closed</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
					</section>

