								<li>Many insurance policies require annual testing</li>
								<li>State athletic associations may mandate testing</li>
								<li>NCAA requires testing for championship events</li>
								<li>Professional leagues have strict testing protocols</li>
								<li>Recommended after significant field repairs</li>
							</ul>

							<div class="warning-box">
								<h3>Liability Protection</h3>
								<p><strong>Critical:</strong> Having current GMAX test results can be crucial in defending against injury lawsuits. Courts increasingly expect athletic programs to demonstrate proactive safety measures.</p>
							</div>

							<h3>Documentation Requirements</h3>
							<p>Proper GMAX testing provides legally defensible documentation that shows:</p>
							<ul>
								<li>You took reasonable steps to ensure player safety</li>
								<li>Your field met industry safety standards</li>
								<li>You followed professional maintenance protocols</li>
								<li>You have objective data to support safety claims</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
					</section>

